  "prompt": "How do I set a default font in Gmail?",
  "response": "To set a default font in Gmail, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open Gmail in your web browser\n\n2. Click the gear icon (Settings) in the top right corner\n\n3. Select \"See all settings\"\n\n4. Go to the \"General\" tab\n\n5. Scroll down to the \"Default text style\" section\n\n6. Choose your preferred font, size, and color from the dropdown menus\n\n7. Click \"Save Changes\" at the bottom of the page\n\nNote: This will change the default font for new emails you compose. Existing emails and received emails will not be affected.\n\nIf you want to change the font for a specific email while composing, you can use the font formatting toolbar in the compose window.",
